title: TidGi Feature Handbook/AI Assistant/Configure External AI API
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Open TidGi settings (click the gear icon at the bottom of the sidebar), find "External API Settings", and configure the following model endpoints:

!! Language Model (Conversations / Agents)

Fill in an OpenAI-compatible Base URL and API Key. For example:

* Official OpenAI: `https://api.openai.com/v1`
* Local Ollama: `http://localhost:11434/v1`
* Any compatible endpoint (DeepSeek, Azure OpenAI, etc.) works

!! Embedding Model (Vector Semantic Search)

Used to generate vector indexes for tiddlers. Can use a different endpoint or model name from the language model. Must be configured separately.

!! Speech Model (Voice-to-Text)

Used to transcribe audio recordings before sending to an agent. Fill in an OpenAI Whisper-compatible endpoint and model name.

!! Tips

* Once configured, go to [[TidGi Feature Handbook/AI Assistant/Using Agents]] to start a conversation.
* Leave a section blank if you don't need that model type.
